cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.DS 

This paper focuses on the formalisation of a programming language construct for local variables in the context of concurrent programs. This makes it likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with the formalisation of concurrency and shared variables, which makes it relevant to the Software Engineering (cs.SE), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories.
